headline: ON Q1 Earnings Call: Auto Weakness, Industrial Stabilization, and Cost Actions Shape Outlook
summary: Analog chips maker onsemi (NASDAQ:ON) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 22.4% year on year to $1.45 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $1.45 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.55 per share was 9.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
